posts.body: Either try deleting the data folder or if that don't work just delete the whole zeronet folder and reinstall.

>>f9569716-b5b8-4514-a995-d2fb1023c9de
I couldn't be bothered to mess around trying to figure out what would work so i chose the latter. Fixed it all for me. Just had the issue where it returns an error if you try to download as archive, which i solved by double checking 0net was up-to-date which it wasn't even though the menu said it was.
